web art-decor.org Initially the implementation guide was build up based on the CDA-CH-VACD - Immunization Content (eVACDOC) ART-DECOR® specification which has been published by eHealth Suisse . CDA-CH-VACD - Immunization Content (eVACDOC) defines the documents for the exchange of immunization and vaccination information. The documents are based on the IHE Technical Framework â€žPatient Care Coordination (PCC)â€œ with the profile â€žImmunization Content (IC)â€œ. The IHE PCC himself references the HL7 Clinical Document Architecture (CDA).

web www.fedlex.admin.ch The flag mustSupport demands that the content creator must support these elements if they are known. If the sending application has data for the element, it is required to populate the element with a non-empty value. If the value is not known, the element may be omitted. A receiving application may ignore the information conveyed by the element. A receiving application shall not raise an error solely due to the presence or absence of the element. For more information about the exchange format see EPD Anhang 4 Austauschformate .
